===============================================================================
| GematriaFBC 1.2; A simple gematria calculator - console ver.                |
|      readme file                                                            |
===============================================================================
This package contains 7 FreeBASIC file:

1 Main Program (./):
GematriaM.bas

6 Translation Units (./units):
Chaldean.bas
Jewish.bas
Pythag.bas
Reduced.bas
Septenary.bas
SimpleAndReg.bas

===============================================================================
| User guide                                                                  |
===============================================================================
#####################
#   Installation    #
#####################
Linux 32- and 64-bit and Windows (32-bit) binaries are included in the Git
repository (/bin/ folder).  Each have -x86,-amd64, or .exe respectively.   If
you are unsure which Linux binary you need, download the -x86 version.

To compile on Linux:
fbc ./GematriaFBC.bas

To compile on Windows:
fbc GematriaFBC.bas

(Binaries compiled with FB version 1.02.1)

#########################
#  Running the Program  #
#########################
Linux:
It is suggested to make a symbolic link to the binary in /home/foo/bin/, that
way the program can be run from anywhere.

Windows:
Double click the .exe or call the program from the command prompt.


Usage:
     -h, --help              Show options
     -v, --version           Show version
     -l, --log               Log session (as GematriaFBC.log)
     -w, --warranty          Warranty and license conditions
     -V, --verbose           Verbose output

#########################
#  General Information  #
#########################
Enter a phrase to find the gematria.  Enter !q to quit.
Gives Simple English, Regular English, Jewish, Septenary, Chaldean, Pythagorian
and Reduced.
Note that the verbose option comes at a cost of speed, but will display the
entered string and then letter values in a sum format.  This is good for those
whose are learning the values of letters in the different systems.
As of version 1.0, the program will calculate dates and numbers, which had
previously been ignored.


Example (terse):
:> GematriaFBC
Simple:      85
Regular:     510
Jewish:      244
Septenary:   43
Chaldean:    34
Pythagorian: 49
Reduced:     4


Example (verbose):
:> GematriaFBC
Simple:      85
Regular:     510
G  E  M  A  T  R  I  A  F  B  C
7 +5 +13+1 +20+18+9 +1 +6 +2 +3
G   E   M   A   T   R   I   A   F   B   C
42 +30 +78 +6  +120+108+54 +6  +36 +12 +18

Jewish:      244
G   E   M   A   T   R   I   A   F   B   C
7  +5  +30 +1  +100+80 +9  +1  +6  +2  +3

Septenary:   43
G E M A T R I A F B C
7+5+1+1+7+5+5+1+6+2+3

Chaldean:    34
G E M A T R I A F B C
3+5+4+1+4+2+1+1+8+2+3

Pythagorian: 49
G E M A T R I A F B C
7+5+4+1+2+9+9+1+6+2+3

Reduced:     4
4+9
